The paper deals with the development of a new approach for identifying customers registered in an investment bank, which is a task related to database management. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of anti-money laundering solutions, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The approach presented in the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the processing time of the database system architecture, which is a topic related to computer systems (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of real-world datasets, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
